{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1781115467134,"sessionID":"ses_14d563d02ffe5XuqIsJCwFy9nr","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_j8tikixr","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"README.md","content":"# Temperature Conversion Library\n\nA simple library for converting temperatures between Celsius, Fahrenheit, and Kelvin.\n\n## Installation\n\nTo install the library, run:\n\n```bash\npip install .\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nThe library includes a CLI tool for temperature conversion. Example usage:\n\n```bash\npython cli.py 100 --from celsius --to fahrenheit\n# Output: 100 celsius is equal to 212.0 fahrenheit\n\npython cli.py 32 --from fahrenheit --to celsius\n# Output: 32 fahrenheit is equal to 0.0 celsius\n\npython cli.py 0 --from celsius --to kelvin\n# Output: 0 celsius is equal to 273.15 kelvin\n```\n\nSupported conversions:\n- Celsius → Fahrenheit\n- Celsius → Kelvin\n- Fahrenheit → Celsius\n\n## Project Structure\n\n- `converters.py`: Contains the core temperature conversion functions (`celsius_to_fahrenheit`, `fahrenheit_to_celsius`, `celsius_to_kelvin`).\n- `cli.py`: Implements the command-line interface using `argparse`.\n- `test_converters.py`: Unit tests for the conversion functions.\n- `test_cli.py`: Tests for the CLI tool, including error handling for invalid units and unsupported conversions."},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/Users/nathangreen/Development/eddi-lab/llm-orc/scratch/spike-sigma-premature-finish/j3_diag/ws2/README.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"scratch/spike-sigma-premature-finish/j3_diag/ws2/README.md","time":{"start":1781115467123,"end":1781115467133}},"id":"prt_eb2c13564001e3LHg0H87DpzyX","sessionID":"ses_14d563d02ffe5XuqIsJCwFy9nr","messageID":"msg_eb2be95bc00121q3DoHivdi3L7"}}
